{"meta":{"authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}],"title":"","dates":{"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:14:26 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:14:26 UTC"}},"nodes":[{"index":0,"parent_index":-1,"body":"<p class=\"Paragraph\">The copulas <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཡོད་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">འདུག་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཡོད་རེད་</span>, etc. are not used in future constructions. Instead, the future forms of the full verbs <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཆགས་</span> &ldquo;to become,&rdquo; <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">བྱེད་</span> &ldquo;to do,&rdquo; <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཡོང་ </span>&ldquo;to come,&rdquo;<a name=\"n1\" href=\"#fn1\">[1]</a> and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">བསྡད་ </span>&ldquo;to stay&rdquo; are used. A distinction may be made between essential and existential statements.</p>\n<hr size=\"1\" />\n<p><a name=\"fn1\" href=\"#n1\">[1]</a> Note that <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཡོང་</span> may also mean &ldquo;to be appropriate.&rdquo;</p>","title":""}]}